            },
            "answer_text": "Always in life? Nothing, but my phone with music. Yeah, I even listen to my own music. Call me pathetic if you want. To a show, I obviously always take my guitar, gig bag, and tuner. If I\u2019m playing electric, I always take my own amp, which may or may not be frowned upon, but I do like a certain sound and want to be able to dial in with no fuss. I always take my own cables and nail clippers. The cables aren\u2019t needed that often, but they are there just in case. An extra set of batteries for my acoustic, and that\u2019s about everything I need. I play with my fingers so I never need to take strings, though I do put on fresh strings the day of the show. ",
